From 0aab3446dd45750706f106f86bb8697b97cf4ceb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Russ W. Knize" <Russ.Knize@motorola.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Apr 2013 16:21:43 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] CHROMIUM: fs: Import esdfs code

This patch adds esdfs code and fixes compilation errors
for 4.14:

* Import esdfs
  Adds esdfs, or the Emulated SD Card file system for
  Android, which replaces the FUSE-backed sdcard service.

  This includes the following patches:
  IKSWM-3291: fs: rename wrapfs to esdfs
  IKSWM-3291: esdfs: emulated SD card storage for Android
  IKSWM-3291: esdfs: add package-derived permission support
  IKSWM-3291: esdfs: unified derived permissions support
  IKSWM-3291: esdfs: add support for Android/media tree
  IKSWM-3291: esdfs: improve support for SELinux
  IKSWM-449: esdfs: remove split permission support
  IKSWM-449: esdfs: add support for multiple storage views
  IKSWL-32765 esdfs: use vmalloc for big package_list_buffer
  IKSWM-2069: esdfs: set proper permisison for root inode
  IKSWM-4710: esdfs: check the hash table, even when unrestricted
  IKSWM-10934: esdfs: override creds for vm operations
  IKSWM-10934: esdfs: override creds for all file descriptor opertaions
  IKSWM-24948: esdfs: parse the Android user ID from the correct root
  IKSWM-25449 esdfs: drop shared caches to reclaim inodes
  IKSWM-31225 esdfs: truncate inode for all 3 mount points.
  IKSWM-31344 esdfs: store lower file in vm_file for mmap
  IKSWM-36499 esdfs: keep a counter for mmaped file
  IKSWM-37275 esdfs: disable access before umount
  IKSWM-38318 esdfs: checking disable access in more functions
  IKSWM-42720 esdfs: fix ext4_releasepage panic
  IKSWM-43295 esdfs: Fix race when create file on lower entry
  esdfs: support lower's own hash
  fs: esdfs: fix race in esdfs unlink
  fs: esdfs: fix deadlock between rmdir and lookup
  fs: esdfs: check if parent changed in rmdir/unlink
  esdfs: don't relax permissions on unconfined public volumes
  [PATCH] IKSWN-28119 esdfs: add lock for setting new size
  IKSWN-19224 esdfs: support case-insensitive

  (cherry picked from commit 4854332d180758def7b7742289d34a425c87c614)
  Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/791975

* Port to 4.4:
  - Removed aio_{write|read}.
  - Fixed function signatures.

  (cherry picked from commit 06c16e9342ca626fba25024dab38a27f274c8f44)
  Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/792495

* Port to 4.14:
  - Add zero salt to init_name_hash and full_name_hash.
  - inodes now use i_rwsem for locking, change all mutex_{lock,unlock}*
    (inode->i_mutex) to inode_{lock,unlock}*(inode).
  - inode_change_ok --> setattr_prepare.
  - change definitions for esdfs_{compare| rename| getattr|
    direct_IO} to match equivalent vfs_ops.
  - change definitions for esdfs_{fault | page_mkwrite} to
    match equivalent vm_ops.

BUG=b:63876697
TEST=compilation, mount esdfs

